<subSubSection id="C36765143E2AFFB6C5F6327D9FAAFAA7" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC2369F3E2AFFB6C5F6327D9FAAFAA7" blockId="0.[136,1452,1504,2069]" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C5F6327D9A5BFA6E" bold="true" box="[189,299,1576,1600]" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">Diagnosis</emphasis>
:—Plants of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2AFFB6C4F9327C99EDFA6F" box="[434,669,1577,1601]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" isHybrid="true" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="siljakii">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C4F9327C994EFA6E" box="[434,574,1577,1600]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">Urospermum</emphasis>
× 
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C71F327C99EDFA6F" box="[596,669,1577,1601]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">siljakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are intermediate between 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2AFFB6C6FD327C9F2BFA6F" authorityName="Scopoli ex Schmidt" authorityYear="1795" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[950,1115,1577,1601]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dalechampii">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C6FD327C9F2BFA6F" box="[950,1115,1577,1601]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">U. dalechampii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2AFFB6C1C4327C9E62FA6F" authorityName="Scopoli ex Schmidt" authorityYear="1795" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[1167,1298,1577,1601]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picroides">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C1C4327C9E62FA6F" box="[1167,1298,1577,1601]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">U. picroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in most traits. They differ from parental species by the consistency of indumentum, that is not as softly hairy as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2AFFB6C1F532189E13FA4B" authorityName="Scopoli ex Schmidt" authorityYear="1795" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[1214,1379,1613,1637]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dalechampii">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C1F532189E13FA4B" box="[1214,1379,1613,1637]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">U. dalechampii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nor as strongly hispid and spinulose as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2AFFB6C4B4322499F1FAA7" authorityName="Scopoli ex Schmidt" authorityYear="1795" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[511,641,1649,1673]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picroides">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C4B4322499F1FAA7" box="[511,641,1649,1673]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">U. picroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a trait particularly noticeable on the involucrum bracts.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36765143E2AFFB7C5F632C199B4FB56" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="221" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC2369F3E2AFFB6C5F632C199D9F43B" blockId="0.[136,1452,1504,2069]" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C5F632C19A31FA82" bold="true" box="[189,321,1684,1708]" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">Description</emphasis>
:—Annual to perennial herb. 
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C73F32C099D8FA82" box="[628,680,1685,1708]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">Stem</emphasis>
sometimes prostrate in its lowest part, vegetative and sparingly branched, then upright. 
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C45C32EC9A11FAFE" box="[279,353,1721,1744]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">Leaves</emphasis>
entire to pinnatifid, with hispid and spinulose trichomes at least on the veins beneath. 
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C1B732EC9EDCFAFF" box="[1276,1452,1721,1745]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">Flowering shoot</emphasis>
with usually 0–3 branches restricted to the first order as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2AFFB6C65A328898C7FADB" authorityName="Scopoli ex Schmidt" authorityYear="1795" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[785,951,1757,1781]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dalechampii">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C65A328898C7FADB" box="[785,951,1757,1781]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">U. dalechampii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2AFFB6C10F32889FB8FADB" authorityName="Scopoli ex Schmidt" authorityYear="1795" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[1092,1224,1757,1781]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picroides">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C10F32889FB8FADB" box="[1092,1224,1757,1781]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">U. picroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it may present more branches (up to&gt; 20) and of higher order. 
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C720335499B8FB37" box="[619,712,1793,1817]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">Capitula</emphasis>
<quantity id="4C859B7A3E2AFFB6C79833559839FB36" box="[723,841,1792,1816]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="32.5" valueMax="45.0" valueMin="20.0">20–45 mm</quantity>
wide (
<quantity id="4C859B7A3E2AFFB6C6D333549F60FB36" box="[920,1040,1793,1817]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="55.0" valueMax="70.0" valueMin="40.0">40–70 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2AFFB6C17233549F91FB37" authorityName="Scopoli ex Schmidt" authorityYear="1795" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[1081,1249,1793,1817]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dalechampii">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C17233549F91FB37" box="[1081,1249,1793,1817]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">U. dalechampii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<quantity id="4C859B7A3E2AFFB6C1B933549E18FB36" box="[1266,1384,1793,1817]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="20.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="10.0">10–30 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2AFFB6C0DA33549B9AFB13" authorityName="Scopoli ex Schmidt" authorityYear="1795" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picroides">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C0DA33549B9AFB13" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">U. picroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), on long peduncles. 
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C4923370994EFB13" box="[473,574,1829,1853]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">Involucre</emphasis>
of generally eight bracts of equal length arranged in a row and connate in their lower third, covered by a slight indumentum of hispid and spinulose trichomes. 
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C6A6331C9F5FFB4F" box="[1005,1071,1865,1889]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">Floret</emphasis>
number per capitulum closer to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2AFFB6C0DA331C9B9AFBAB" authorityName="Scopoli ex Schmidt" authorityYear="1795" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picroides">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C0DA331C9B9AFBAB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">U. picroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(&lt;150) than to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2AFFB6C4D633389932FBAB" authorityName="Scopoli ex Schmidt" authorityYear="1795" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[413,578,1901,1925]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dalechampii">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C4D633389932FBAB" box="[413,578,1901,1925]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">U. dalechampii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(&gt; 150). Ligules yellow, sometimes with a dark mark at the apex of petals and a purplish stripe on the outer face. 
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C4A633C4995AFB87" box="[493,554,1937,1961]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">Seeds</emphasis>
not developed, suggesting that the hybrid is likely sterile. 
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C1E833C49EF9FB87" box="[1187,1417,1937,1961]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">Chromosome number</emphasis>
2n = 12, intermediate between that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2AFFB6C74D33E099DCFBE3" authorityName="Scopoli ex Schmidt" authorityYear="1795" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[518,684,1973,1997]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dalechampii">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C74D33E099DCFBE3" box="[518,684,1973,1997]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">U. dalechampii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(2n = 14) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2AFFB6C61A33E098A5FBE3" authorityName="Scopoli ex Schmidt" authorityYear="1795" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[849,981,1973,1997]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picroides">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C61A33E098A5FBE3" box="[849,981,1973,1997]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">U. picroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(2n = 10). 
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C11833E09FACFBE2" box="[1107,1244,1973,1996]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">Genome size</emphasis>
(i.e., nuclear DNA content) of 2C = 1.89 pg ± 0.01, corresponding to the average value between the genome size of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2AFFB6C1C5338C9E42FBDF" authorityName="Scopoli ex Schmidt" authorityYear="1795" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[1166,1330,2009,2033]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dalechampii">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C1C5338C9E42FBDF" box="[1166,1330,2009,2033]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">U. dalechampii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(2C = 2.26 pg. ± 0.01) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2AFFB6C47A33A89AC3F43B" authorityName="Scopoli ex Schmidt" authorityYear="1795" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[305,435,2045,2069]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picroides">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2AFFB6C47A33A89AC3F43B" box="[305,435,2045,2069]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">U. picroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(2C = 1.51 pg ± 0.01).
</paragraph>
