<paragraph id="8BC2369F3E2BFFB7C5F632F99810FAC6" blockId="1.[136,1452,1708,1912]" pageId="1" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2BFFB7C5F632F99A1DFAEA" bold="true" box="[189,365,1708,1732]" pageId="1" pageNumber="221">Flowering time</emphasis>
:—The phenology of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2BFFB7C71432F8983DFAEA" box="[607,845,1708,1732]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" isHybrid="true" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="221" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="siljakii">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2BFFB7C71432F8999BFAEA" box="[607,747,1709,1732]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="221">Urospermum</emphasis>
× 
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2BFFB7C64F32F9983DFAEA" box="[772,845,1708,1732]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="221">siljakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to its parent species 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2BFFB7C1E532F89E26FAEA" box="[1198,1366,1708,1732]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="221" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dalechampii">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2BFFB7C1E532F89E26FAEA" box="[1198,1366,1708,1732]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="221">U. dalechampii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2BFFB7C0DA32F89B9AFAC6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="221" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picroides">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2BFFB7C0DA32F89B9AFAC6" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="221">U. picroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, all of them flowering mostly in spring from April to June.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC2369F3E2BFFB7C5F632A199B4FB56" blockId="1.[136,1452,1708,1912]" pageId="1" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2BFFB7C5F632A19A58FB22" bold="true" box="[189,296,1780,1804]" pageId="1" pageNumber="221">Eponymy</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2BFFB7C40132A09941FB22" box="[330,561,1780,1804]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Urospermum" isHybrid="true" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="221" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="siljakii">
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2BFFB7C40132A09AA2FB22" box="[330,466,1781,1804]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="221">Urospermum</emphasis>
× 
<emphasis id="B909EA8D3E2BFFB7C4A732A19941FB22" box="[492,561,1780,1804]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="221">siljakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named after Prof. Sonja Siljak-Yakovlev (
<collectingRegion id="49B9F87D3E2BFFB7C16D32A19F14FB22" box="[1062,1124,1780,1804]" country="Serbia" name="Vrsac" pageId="1" pageNumber="221">Vršac</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36A760F3E2BFFB7C13F32A19FC8FB22" box="[1140,1208,1780,1804]" name="Serbia" pageId="1" pageNumber="221">Serbia</collectingCountry>
, 
<date id="FFC3105F3E2BFFB7C18332A19EE2FB22" box="[1224,1426,1780,1804]" pageId="1" pageNumber="221" value="1946-09-08">
<collectingDate id="EF87E9B73E2BFFB7C18332A19EE2FB22" box="[1224,1426,1780,1804]" pageId="1" pageNumber="221" value="1946-09-08">8 September 1946</collectingDate>
</date>
–), 
<location id="8EA260443E2BFFB7C5C3334D9A9EFB1E" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03D487893E2AFFB7C5C3312699B4FB56:8EA260443E2BFFB7C5C3334D9A9EFB1E" box="[136,494,1816,1840]" country="Serbia" name="Directeur de Recherche Emerite" pageId="1" pageNumber="221" stateProvince="Vrsac">Directeur de Recherche Emérite</location>
at the Université Paris-Saclay, 
<collectingCountry id="F36A760F3E2BFFB7C61E334C98D0FB1E" box="[853,928,1817,1840]" name="France" pageId="1" pageNumber="221">France</collectingCountry>
, a botanist with a longstanding interest in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1C3E2BFFB7C5C333699A71FB7A" box="[136,257,1852,1876]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="221" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
. She has been mentor to many researchers working on karyology and cytogenetics, sparing no time and effort to train and connect researchers from all over the world.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
